<Review ID>1670975
<Product Name>Creative Zen Micro 6 GB MP3 Player Dark Blue
<Title>Not so good
<Date>Tue Feb 21 00:00:00 CST 2006
<Content>I only bought this one instead of an iPod because it works with Rhapsody. The product has been a little disappointing, here's the pros and cons:  Pros:  + Looks good. + Sounds good. + Very handy.  Cons:  - Quality: had to ask for replacement after jack failed. - Skips: Almost all the music I have, I got it from Rhapsody, so it seems sometimes the device has to check for track license or something before playing, so this produces an annoying skip between songs, sometimes more than 3 seconds. - Most of the time it doesn't work quite well with Rhapsody software, sometimes it freezes when trying to upload songs, and have to restart the program or unplug the device from my computer. - Battery life is not really good, and I use it with volume 10 (out of 25) and don't mess a lot with the controls.  Another con, related with this product, although not rated here, is the beltclip, is a really cheap piece of plastic that breaks easily, although got a replacement after the first one broke, that one also broke, so now I'm waiting for a second replacement, although this time I asked for a leather poucher.  Finally, if you are a music fan, you might find this product, combined with a music service (e.g. Rhapsody, Napster) very enjoyable, if it doesn't break of course.  
<Overall>3

